  line `[The Standing Committee of the Academic Council.] Omitted by the Banaras Hindu University`
  line `(Amendment) Act (34 of 1969), s. 7 (w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (40824)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 18
  title `Other authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 12, for section 12A (w.e.f. 31-12-1951).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40824&sectionno=12A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Other authorities.--Subject to the provisions of the this Act, the functions, powers and`
  line `duties of the other authorities of the University shall be provided for by the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_b:
  sectionId (40825)
  sectionNo 12B
  orderNo 19
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 12, for section 12A (w.e.f. 31-12-1951).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40825&sectionno=12B&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_12_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[12B. Disqualifications.--(1) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen as, and for being`
  line `a member of any of the authorities of the University--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is of unsound mind or is a deaf-mute or suffers from contagious leprosy;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(c) if he has been convicted by a Court of law of an offence involving moral turpitude and`
  line `sentenced in respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether a person is or had been subjected to any of the`
  line `disqualifications mentioned in sub-section (1), the question shall be referred for the decision of the Visitor`
  line `and his decision shall be final, and no suit or other proceeding shall lie in any Court of law against such`
  line decision.]
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (40826)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 20
  title `Audit of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40826&sectionno=13&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The accounts of the University shall, once at least in every year and at`
  line `intervals of not more than fifteen months, be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.]`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts, when audited, shall be published in the Official Gazette and a copy of the accounts,`
  line `together with the auditor's reports, shall be ^2[submitted ^3*** to the Visitor].`
  line
  line `^4[(3) A copy of the accounts, together with the auditors report, shall also be submitted to the Central`
  line `Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1951, s. 9, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 13, for "submitted to the Visitor" (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. The words "to the Court and" omitted by Act 34 of 1969, s. 8 (w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 25 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-12-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (40827)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 21
  title `Annual Report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-12-2008).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40827&sectionno=13A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Annual Report.--(1) The annual report of the University shall be prepared under the`
  line `direction of the Executive Council and shall be submitted to the Court on or before such date as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes and shall be considered by the Court in its annual meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may communicate its comments thereon to the Executive Council.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the annual report, as prepared under sub-section (1), shall also be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.]
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (40828)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 22
  title `Permanent reserve to cover recurring charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40828&sectionno=14&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The University shall invest, and keep`
  line `invested, in securities in which trust funds may be invested, in accordance with the provisions of the law`
  line `relating to trusts in ^1[India], a sum of ^2[forty-five lakhs of rupees] as a permanent endowment to meet the`
  line `recurring charges of the University other than charges in respect of scholarships, prizes and rewards:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(1) any Government securities, as defined by the Indian Securities Act, ^3[1920] which may be`
  line `held by the University shall, for the purpose of this section, be reckoned at their face-value, and`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^4[the aforesaid sum of forty-five lakhs shall be reduced by such sum as, at the commencement`
  line `of the Banaras Hindu University (Amendment) Act, 1966 (52 of 1966)] the Central Government`
  line `shall, by order in writing, declare to be the total capitalised value, for the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) of all permanent recurring grants of money which have been made to the University ^5by[any Ruler of any Indian State] and`
  line
  line `(b) of the total income accruing from immovable property which has been transferred to the`
  line University.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1951, s. 10, for "the States" (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 14, for "fifty lakhs of rupees" (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "1886" (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "the aforesaid sum of fifty lakhs shall be reduced by such sum as, at the commencement of this Act"`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "by any Indian Prince or Chief" (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (40829)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 23
  title `Maintenance and admission to privileges of Colleges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40829&sectionno=15&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Hindu`
  line `College, ^1[Banaras], shall, from such ^2date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint in this behalf, be deemed to be a College maintained by the University, and the`
  line `University may found and maintain other colleges and ^3[institutions including High Schools, within a`
  line `radius of fifteen miles from the main temple of the University] for the purpose of carrying out instruction`
  line `and research.`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) The University may also found and maintain (within or beyond the aforementioned limits)`
  line `special centers and laboratories for research in Humanities, Science and Technology, Education,`
  line `Medicine and other professional subjects and in other spheres of learning and knowledge.]`
  line
  line `(2) With the approval of the ^5[Academic Council] and the sanction of the Visitor, and subject to the`
  line `Statutes and ^6[Ordinances] the University may admit colleges and ^7[institutions including High Schools,`
  line `within the aforementioned limits] to such privileges of the University, subject to such conditions, as it`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that no new college or institution started after the commencement of the Banaras Hindu`
  line `University (Amendment) Act, 1966, shall be admitted to any such privileges of the University.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1951, s. 2, for "Benares" (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
  line
  line `2. 1st October, 1917, see Gazette of india, 1917, Pr. I, P. 1641.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 55 of 1951, s. 11, for "institutions in Benares" (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 15 (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 55 of 1951, s. 2, for "Senate" (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Regulations" (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "institutions in Benares" (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (40830)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 24
  title `Recognition of degrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40830&sectionno=16&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions`
  line `granted by the University, shall be recognized by ^1[the Central and State Governments] to the same extent`
  line `and, in the same manner as the corresponding degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic`
  line `distinctions granted by any other University incorporated by ^2[a Central Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "any Government in British India".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "an act of the Central Legislature".`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (40831)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 25
  title `Pension or Provident Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40831&sectionno=16A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Pension or Provident Fund.--The University shall constitute for the benefit of its officers,`
  line `teachers and other ^2[employees] such pension or provident fund ^3[or provide such insurance scheme] as`
  line `it may deem fit in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1930, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 14, for "servants" (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 55 of 1951, s. 12 (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b:
  sectionId (40832)
  sectionNo 16B
  orderNo 26
  title `Conditions of service of officers and teachers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 17 (w.e.f. 31-12-1966)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40832&sectionno=16B&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[16B. Conditions of service of officers and teachers.--(1) Every salaried officer and teacher of`
  line `the University shall be appointed under a written contract, which shall be lodged with the University and`
  line `a copy of which shall be furnished to the officer or teacher concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the University and any of its officers or`
  line `teachers shall, at the request of the officer or teacher concerned or at the instance of the University, be`
  line `referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Executive Council,`
  line `one member nominated by the officer or the teacher concerned and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final and shall not be questioned in any Court`
  line `of law.`
  line
  line `(4) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any Court of law in respect of any matter which is required by`
  line `sub-section (2) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing contained in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to`
  line `arbitrations under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_c:
  sectionId (40833)
  sectionNo 16C
  orderNo 27
  title `Proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 17 (w.e.f. 31-12-1966)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40833&sectionno=16C&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_16_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[16C. Proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc.--No act or proceedings of any authority`
  line `or board or committee of the University shall be invalid merely by reason, of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution thereof, or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the election, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member thereof, or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_d:
  sectionId (40834)
  sectionNo 16D
  orderNo 28
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 17 (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40834&sectionno=16D&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_16_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[16D. Protection of action taken in good faith.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any officer, teacher or other employee of the University for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done by hi m under this Act or the Statutes or the Ordinances or the Regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (40835)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 29
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40835&sectionno=17&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Statutes.--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of`
  line `the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution of the Court and the constitution, powers and duties of the other authorities of`
  line `the University other than the powers and duties provided for in this Act;`
  line
  line `(b)`
  line `^2[the appointment by election, nomination or otherwise] of members of the authorities of the`
  line `University, their continuance in office, the filling of vacancies of members thereof and all other`
  line `matters relating to the authorities;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment, powers and duties of the officers of the University;`
  line
  line `(d) the institution of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions;`
  line
  line `(e) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(f) the holding of convocation to confer degrees;`
  line
  line `(g) the establishment, reconstitution, amalgamation, division or abolition of faculties,`
  line
  line `departments, hostels, colleges and institutions;`
  line
  line `(h) the withdrawal of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions;`
  line
  line `(i) conditions under which colleges and institutions including High Schools may be admitted to`
  line `the privileges of the University and the withdrawal of such privileges;`
  line
  line `(j) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(k) the registration of graduates and the maintenance of a register of registered graduates;`
  line
  line `(l) the classification and the manner of appointment of teachers in the University and the colleges;`
  line
  line `(m) the constitution of a pension or provident fund and the establishment of an insurance scheme`
  line `for the benefit of the officers, teachers and other employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(n) the meetings of the Court, the Executive Council, the Academic Council, ^3*** the Finance`
  line `Committee or the Faculties, the quorum at such meetings and the procedure to be followed in the`
  line `conduct of their bus iness;`
  line
  line `(o) the discipline of students;`
  line
  line `(p) all other matters which are to be or may be provided for by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Statutes in force at the commencement of the Banaras Hindu University (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1966 (52 of 1966), shall be those set out in the Schedule to this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The Executive Council may, from time to time, make new or additional statutes or may amend`
  line `or repeal the Statutes.]`
  line
  line `^5[(4)] Every new Statute or addition to a Statute or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall require`
  line `the previous approval of the Visitor who may sanction or disallow it or remit it for further consideration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 18, for section 17 (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 34 of 1969, s. 9, for "the election and appointment"(w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
  line
  line `3. The words "the Standing Committee of the Academic Council" omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 34 of 1969, s. 9, for sub-sections (3), (4), (5) and (6) (w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
  line
  line `5 Sub-section (7) renumbered as sub-section (4) thereof by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (40836)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 30
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40836&sectionno=18&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Ordinances.--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of students to the University and their enrolment as such;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and certificates of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `^2[(c) the qualifications for admission to courses of study for degrees, diplomas, certificates`
  line `and other academic distinctions and to examinations of the University and the award of degrees,`
  line `diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions;]`
  line
  line `(d) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the University and for admission to the`
  line `examinations, degrees and diplomas of the University;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions of the award of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, exhibitions, medals and`
  line prizes;
  line
  line `(f) the conduct of examinations, including the terms of office and manner of appointment and the`
  line `duties of examining bodies, examiners and moderators;`
  line
  line `^3[(ff) the remunerations and allowances to examiners, moderators and other persons engaged in`
  line `the business of the University;]`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the University;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions of residence of students at the University;`
  line
  line `(i) the special arrangements, if any, which may be made for the residence, discipline and teaching`
  line `of women students, and the prescribing for them of special courses of study;`
  line
  line `(j) the giving of religious instruction;`
  line
  line `(k) the emoluments and the terms and conditions of service of ^4[employees] of the University:`
  line
  line `(l) the management of colleges and other institutions founded or maintained under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 15;`
  line
  line `^3[(ll) the meetings of any board or committee that may be set up under this Act or the Statutes, the`
  line `quorum at such meetings and the procedure to be followed in the conduct of their business;]`
  line
  line `(m) the supervision and inspection of colleges and other institutions admitted to privileges of the`
  line `University under sub-section (2) of section 15; ^5***`
  line
  line `^6[(mm) the powers and duties of teachers and salaried officers and the powers which may be`
  line `delegated to them;`
  line
  line `(mmm) the conditions and qualifications for the registration of graduates;]`
  line
  line `(n) all other matters which by this Act or the Statutes are to be or may be provided for by`
  line `the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(2) The Regulations of the University as in force immediately before the commencement of`
  line `the Banaras Hindu University (Amendment) Act, 1951 (55 of 1951), shall be deemed to be the`
  line `first Ordinances made under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The said Ordinances may be amended, repealed or added to at any time by the Executive Council:`
  line
  line `^7[Provided that no Ordinance shall be made--`
  line
  line `(a) regarding the recognition of examinations of other Universities and institutions as equivalent`
  line `to the University examinations, or`
  line
  line `(b) affecting the conditions, mode of appointment or duties of examiners or the conduct or`
  line `standard of examinations or of any course of study,`
  line
  line `unless a draft of such Ordinance has been proposed by the Academic Council.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Executive Council shall not have power to amend any draft proposed by the Academic`
  line `Council under the provisions of sub-section (3) but may reject the proposal or return the draft to the`
  line `Academic Council for reconsideration, either in whole or in part, together with any amendments which`
  line `the Executive Council may suggest.`
  line
  line `^8[(5) Where the Executive Council has rejected the draft of an Ordinance proposed by the Academic`
  line `Council, the Academic Council may appeal to the Visitor who may pass such order thereon as he thinks`
  line fit.
  line
  line `(6) All Ordinances made by the Executive Council shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the`
  line `Visitor who may disallow any such Ordinance or remit it to the Executive Council for further`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(7) The Visitor may, by order, direct that the operation of any Ordinance shall be suspended until he`
  line `has had an opportunity of exercising his power of disallowance, and any order of suspension under this`
  line `sub-section shall cease to have effect on the expiration of one month from the date of such order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1951, s. 14, for sections 18 and 19 (w.e.f. 3-11-1951).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 19, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "teachers" (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `5. The word "and" omitted by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 19 (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 34 of 1969, s. 10, for sub-sections (5), (6), (7) and (8) (w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (40837)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make Regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40837&sectionno=19&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authorities of the University may make Regulations`
  line `consistent with this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances--`
  line
  line `(a) laying down the procedure to be observed at their meetings and the number of members`
  line `required to form a quorum;`
  line
  line `(b) providing for all matters which by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances are to be prescribed`
  line `by Regulations, and`
  line
  line `(c) providing for all matters solely concerning such authorities or committees appointed by them`
  line `and not provided for by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(2) Every authority of the University shall make Regulations providing for the giving of notice to`
  line `the members of such authority of the dates of meetings and of the business to be considered at meetings`
  line `and for the keeping of a record of the proceedings of meetings.`
  line
  line `(3) The Executive Council may direct the amendment, in such manner as it may specify, of any`
  line `Regulation made under this section or the annulment of any such Regulation:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that any authority of the University which is dissatisfied with any such direction may,`
  line `within two months of the date of such direction, appeal to the ^2[Visitor] whose decision thereon shall be`
  line final.]
  line
  line `^3[(4) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(5) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation or both Houses agree that the Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation should not be made, the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that Statute, Ordinance or Regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 52 of 1966, s. 20, (w.e.f. 31-12-1966). Earlier it was omitted by Act 34 of 1958, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 34 of 1969, s. 6, for "Court" (w.e.f. 5-9-1969).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (40838)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 32
  title `Constitution of boards and committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 52 of 1966, s. 21, for section 19A (w.e.f. 31-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40838&sectionno=19A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Constitution of boards and committees.--Where any authority of the University is given`
  line `power by this Act or by the Statutes to appoint boards or committees, such board or committee shall,`
  line `unless there is some special provision to the contrary, consist of members of the authority concerned and`
  line `of such other persons (if any) as the authority in each case may think fit.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (40839)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 33
  title `Dissolution and transfer of property of the Hindu University Society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197&sectionId=40839&sectionno=20&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00037_191516_1523342355197
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) From`
  line `the commencement of this Act, the Hindu University Society shall be dissolved, and all property,`
  line `movable and immovable, and all rights, powers, and privileges of the Hindu University Society which,`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act, belonged to, or were vested in, the said Society, shall`
  line `vest in the University, and shall be applied to the objects and purposes for which the University is`
  line incorporated.
  line
  line `(2) From the commencement of this Act, all debts and liabilities of the said Society shall be`
  line `transferred and attached to the University, and shall thereafter be discharged and satisfied by the`
  line University.
  line
  line `(3) Any will, deed or other document, whether made or executed before or after the commencement`
  line `of this Act, which contains any bequest, gift or trust in favour of the Central Hindu College or the said`
  line `Society shall, on the commencement of this Act, be construed as if the University were therein named,`
  line `instead of the said College or Society`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
